{
  "texts": [
    "An efficient method for anomaly detection in IDSs is semi-supervised learning, especially when combined with One-Class Support Vector Machines (SVM).",
    "One-Class SVMs are able to establish a border that captures normal network behavior since they are trained on a labeled dataset consisting of only normal data.",
    "When presented with fresh information, they are able to spot outliers that don't fit inside the norm.",
    "Because it makes use of a small bit of labeled data in conjunction with a large number of unlabeled data, this method shines in situations when labeled incursion data is sparse 50.",
    "In this way, intrusion detection systems may keep their false positive rate low while yet successfully detecting new and developing threats."
  ]
}